Considering the synonymies proposed here, 

T. baeticus

is a widespread species throughout the Mediterranean region. It is present across the Iberian Peninsula, the Balearic Islands, Sicily, Tunisia, and the Balkans (
Bănărescu 1991
; 
Bandel 2001
; 
Bank 2006
; 

Feher
and 
Eross
2009

; 
Zettler and van Damme 2010
; 

Martinez-Orti
et al. 2015

; 
Sands et al. 2019a
). Within our study region, the species is only noted from the freshwater drainages of the Gulf of 
Goekova
in south-west Anatolia (Fig. 
3A
).
